To install:

Create a venv in the root directory:

`python -m venv .venv`

If you create the venv in a different directory or call it something other than `.venv` then you will need to update `invoke_weather_report.sh` to activate the correct venv.

Activate the venv now (altering the path if required):
`source ./.venv/bin/activate`

Install build dependencies (just wheel)
`pip install wheel==0.44.0`

Install the package
`pip install .`

Configure environment-specific variables by setting up a .env. The easiest way to do this is to copy the example.env and then edit as required
`cp example.env .env`
`nano .env`

Ensure that both shell scripts are executable
`chmod +x ./scripts/invoke_weather_report.sh && chmod +x ./scripts/schedule_weather_report.sh`

Run the scheduler (edit the cron job to the desired frequency, default * * * * * is every minute)
`./scripts/schedule_weather_report.sh`

All set, the scheduler will run the python script every minute forever. 

To stop this, run (be careful, this will remove all cron jobs):
`crontab -r`